(
Figs 1 – 8
)

Pleopod 2
(
Fig. 8B
) peduncle with 3 coupling hooks; endopod with about 20 plumose setae apically and distally along mesial margin; exopod with around 31 plumose setae apically and along whole lateral margin; appendix masculina (
Fig. 8C
) fused as a single penial plate, styliform, straight, apically bifid, pointing sligthly mediodistally, 1.2 times longer than endopod.

Distribution:
Off 
South Africa
, Agulhas Bank, Still Bay at 
156–200 m
(zur Strassen 1902; 
Kensley 1975
; 
Kensley 1978
).
